docker build -t varunrajdocker/posts . => Build an image based on the dockerfile in current directory and tag it
docker run [image id or image tag] => Create and start a container based on the provided image id or tag
docker run -t [image id or image tag] => Create and start container but also override the default command
docker ps => Print out information about all of the running containers
docker exec -t [container id][cmd] => Execute the given command in a running container
docker logs [container id] => Print out logs from the given container
